<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1261">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/52.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Arizona</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phoenix, Ariz.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In compliance with the request conveyed to me through your telegram of
                            to-day I have the honor to assure you that the State of Arizona readily
                            assents to the transporting of Mexican Federal troops from Ciudad Juárez
                            through United States territory to points in the State of Sonora where
                            American lives and property, are being endangered by the operation of
                            Mexican revolutionary bands.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. W. P. Hunt.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>